From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Herbert Xu <herbert@gondor.apana.org.au>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 23:07:02 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] crypto: af_alg - Fix page reassignment overflow in
 af_alg_pull_tsgl

commit 31d00156e50ecad37f2cb6cbf04aaa9a260505ef upstream.

When page reassignment was added to af_alg_pull_tsgl the original
loop wasn't updated so it may try to reassign one more page than
necessary.

Add the check to the reassignment so that this does not happen.

Also update the comment which still refers to the obsolete offset
argument.

Reported-by: syzbot+d23888375c2737c17ba5@syzkaller.appspotmail.com
Fixes: e870456d8e7c ("crypto: algif_skcipher - overhaul memory management")
Signed-off-by: Herbert Xu <herbert@gondor.apana.org.au>
Signed-off-by: Eric Biggers <ebiggers@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Thomas Lamprecht <t.lamprecht@proxmox.com>
---
 crypto/af_alg.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/crypto/af_alg.c b/crypto/af_alg.c
index cab04b009d037e64f6f8736ad9ad1cc400762587..2c1ec61cfb56370e40ebe0da160ddcafcf588243 100644
--- a/crypto/af_alg.c
+++ b/crypto/af_alg.c
@@ -702,8 +702,8 @@ void af_alg_pull_tsgl(struct sock *sk, size_t used, struct scatterlist *dst)
 			 * Assumption: caller created af_alg_count_tsgl(len)
 			 * SG entries in dst.
 			 */
-			if (dst) {
-				/* reassign page to dst after offset */
+			if (dst && plen) {
+				/* reassign page to dst */
 				get_page(page);
 				sg_set_page(dst + j, page, plen, sg[i].offset);
 				j++;
